Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Vicky López (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Vicky López (pictured) took up horse riding during a six-month period when she was not allowed to play football?

entry.title: Pink Venom (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Blackpink's "Pink Venom" incorporates the sounds of traditional Korean instruments such as the geomungo?

entry.title: Iona Allen (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Iona Allen, "the only one to ever make a perfect pair of boots", constructed the pair worn by Neil Armstrong on the Moon out of thirteen layers of precisely fabricated material?

entry.title: Vostok 2022 (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Vostok 2022 marked the most comprehensive participation of Chinese forces in a Russian military exercise to date?

entry.title: Chandelure (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the chandelier Pokémon Chandelure is a playable character in the fighting game Pokkén Tournament?

entry.title: REM de l'Est (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the REM de l'Est, a planned light rail network, was abandoned due to its controversial use of elevated railways in downtown Montreal?

entry.title: Virtual Self (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Porter Robinson listened to excerpts of 100,000 songs in two years to create his EP Virtual Self?

entry.title: tokoyama (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that tokoyama (traditional Japanese hairdressers) working in kabuki are divided into specialties named after the floors of the Kabuki-za?

entry.title: Puyallup people (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Puyallup people traditionally took ritual sweat baths before hunting, after intercourse, and even as a sport?
